picam (1.1.0) unstable; urgency=medium

  * camview: Raspberry Pi CSI/MIPI support via GStreamer libcamerasrc — GTK 4 live
    preview (gtk4paintablesink); headless still capture (JPEG/PNG); timed H.264
    recording (MP4/MOV/MKV) with hardware encoder preference (v4l2h264enc).
  * camview: 1-based camera index (-i/--device) for dual CSI; optional
    --camera-name; duration parsing (s, ms, min, hr, etc.); resolution, framerate,
    JPEG quality, AF settle and --no-autofocus.
  * debian/control: runtime Depends on gstreamer1.0-libcamera, base/good/bad
    plugins, gstreamer1.0-gtk4, libgtk-4-1; Recommends rpicam-hello |
    libcamera-hello for camera listing; Build-Depends for GLib/GTK/GStreamer dev
    packages.
  * Documentation: README / README-zh; camview(1); bash-completion; GitHub
    homepage in package metadata.
  * tests: duration_test (parse durations), lib_test (stream/file helpers).

 -- Lenik <picam@bodz.net>  Sun, 10 May 2026 12:00:00 +0000

